OL,3,CElizabeth Hurley 'crushed' by
OL,4,Callegation of phone tapping, court told
OL,6,FShe claimed in her written evidence
OL,7,Fthat the Mail had tapped her phone and
OL,8,Frecorded live telephone conversations.
OL,9,FShe also accused them of placing
OL,10,Fsurreptitious microphones on her home
OL,11,Fwindows, stealing medical information
OL,12,Fwhile she was pregnant with her son
OL,13,FDamian, and other "monstrous,
OL,14,Fstaggering things."
OL,16,FWearing a deep green, knitted dress,
OL,17,FHurley became visibly upset in the
OL,18,Fwitness box, crying on several
OL,19,Foccasions as she was taken through a
OL,20,Fnumber of news articles.
